{"sections":[],"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Event Kit and Event Kit UI frameworks together allow iPhone OS applications to access event information from a user’s Calendar database. You can fetch events based on a date range or a unique identifier, receive notifications when event records change, and allow users to create and edit events for any of their local and server-based calendars. Learn techniques to take advantage of these features and other useful tips from Apple engineers."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10-136-Calendar-Integration-with-Event-Kit"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc10-136-calendar-integration-with-event-kit"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2010\/136\/","overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","isActive":true}},"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC10","title":"Calendar Integration with Event Kit","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]}],"references":{"WWDC10.jpeg":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC10.jpeg","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCN